						<summary>

						<p>On the outer <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chaḍaiyavarmaṉ Sundara-pāṇḍya year 13+1:</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription may be assigned to c. 14th century on palaeographical considerations.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the grant of land probably as <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili</hi> by the <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> of Periyakōṭṭai and Kāḍandai-kuḍi to the temple of the deity Tiruvuśāttāṉam-[uḍaiyār]. This document was attested by several signatories including Tiru[mala]pāḍi-uḍaiyār and others. </p>						

						</summary>
